nib.text:
A cat was killed and two people including a firefighter were injured during a house fire in Lyndale Saturday morning, officials said. 

At around 5:30 a.m., firefighters responded to a report of a fire in the 3400 block of Blaisdell Avenue.

Upon arrival, crews discovered a fire on a porch that had spread into the house. 

Firefighters immediately began working to extinguish the blaze.

According to the MFD, firefighters discovered a person on the second floor and rescued them from the blaze. The person was being treated by medics at the scene before they were transported to the hospital. 

Additionally, one firefighter sustained a leg injury after their foot went through the floor.

Firefighters were able to bring the flames under control just after 6 p.m.

Unfortunately, the MFD reported a deceased cat was found in the home. 

Investigators are determining the cause of the blaze.
